Yes — now that your pxe-content image/container project is becoming dynamic, the Ansible role should mainly do one thing cleanly:

It should deploy the container with Quadlet and mount the bundle’s extracted_isos/ directory into the container as /iso.

So the important correction is:

host bundle path:   /path/to/aerolit_bundle/extracted_isos
container path:     /iso

Do not change the container/Nginx side to extracted_isos. Inside the container, /iso is still the clean stable path. The role just needs to mount the right host directory into /iso.

Delete this old file from the role if it still exists:

templates/pxe-content.service.j2

Replace/add these files.

